The '''Deranged archaeologist''' is a relatively simple boss similar to the [[Crazy archaeologist]] and the [[Chaos Fanatic]]; although his special attack has the potential to cause major damage if not avoided. The [[boss]] is located on [[Fossil Island]], at the southern end of the [[Tar Swamp]]. An [[axe]] is required to chop a swamp vine in order to reach him. Directly before the area is a [[Spine mushroom|spine mushroom]] that will occasionally hit passing players for 10 damage and apply [[poison]].

He's nearly identical to the Crazy archaeologist in terms of [[combat]] - he throws books as a [[Ranged]] attack, and punches and kicks players who stand in [[melee]] range. His [[special attack]] is similar but hits much harder (up to 56 damage per direct hit{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1383758002528800771|date=18 April 2021|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/dMzPN|archivedate=18 April 2021|quote=56, I believe.}}, up to 92 damage with a direct and 2 indirect hits), and he shouts "Learn to Read!" when he uses it. Notably, however, the Deranged archaeologist drops none of the same unique items as the crazy archaeologist. As a variant of the crazy archaeologist, the deranged archaeologist can be killed in lieu of the crazy archaeologist if assigned as a slayer task.

[[File:Fighting Deranged archaeologist.png|thumb|left|A player damaged by the deranged archaeologist's special attack.]]

While having slightly better common drops than his crazed counterpart, the deranged archaeologist has fewer, less valuable unique drops. His only exclusive drop is the [[steel ring]], which provides impressive melee defence, even more so than an [[Ring of suffering (i)|imbued ring of suffering]].

