==Trivia==
*Upon release, the Deranged archaeologist dropped uncharged [[Amulet of glory|amulets of glory]] at an uncommon rate. As the amulet of glory is one of the most coveted early-game [[ironman]] items (which has high requirements - either 83 [[Hunter]] to catch [[dragon impling]]s, or 80 [[Crafting]] to create), this caused player complaints about making it far too easy to obtain. This was changed and now he drops [[crystal key]]s instead.
*Upon release, the deranged archaeologist could be [[safespotted]]. His {{overhead|No hiding!}} attack was soon added to counter this. This was removed later after the NPC was given its own dedicated lair.
*His examine text may be a reference to the "Tears in Rain" monologue from the 1982 {{wp|Ridley Scott}} film ''{{wp|Blade Runner}}''.
*Prior to the addition of the [[steel ring]] on [[25 June]] [[2025]], the deranged archaeologist was the only non-quest [[boss]] in ''Old School RuneScape'' to have no unique drops.

